      "message": "This comment about guards is not generally always true (an experiment that didn\u0027t go very far), but between this and the conditional stuff you see starting at :598, Skia should build correctly with an empty sources_assignment_filter.\n\nMaybe we write it like,\n\n# This file (and all GN files in Skia) are designed to work with an\n# empty sources assignment filter; we handle all that explicitly.\n# We clear the filter here for clients who may have set up a global filter.\nset_sources_assignment_filter([])\n\nI don\u0027t think we\u0027d mind moving some files around so that they\u0027re not accidentally filtered out by a reasonable filter list.  What is your filter list?",
