      "message": "The filter used on iOS is:\n\n[\n  \"*_win.cc\"\n  \"*_win.h\"\n  \"*_win_unittest.cc\"\n  \"*\\bwin/*\"\n  \"*.def\"\n  \"*.rc\"\n  \"*_mac.h\"\n  \"*_mac.cc\"\n  \"*_mac.mm\"\n  \"*_mac_unittest.h\"\n  \"*_mac_unittest.cc\"\n  \"*_mac_unittest.mm\"\n  \"*\\bmac/*\"\n  \"*_cocoa.h\"\n  \"*_cocoa.cc\"\n  \"*_cocoa.mm\"\n  \"*_cocoa_unittest.h\"\n  \"*_cocoa_unittest.cc\"\n  \"*_cocoa_unittest.mm\"\n  \"*\\bcocoa/*\"\n  \"*_linux.h\"\n  \"*_linux.cc\"\n  \"*_linux_unittest.h\"\n  \"*_linux_unittest.cc\"\n  \"*\\blinux/*\"\n  \"*_android.h\"\n  \"*_android.cc\"\n  \"*_android_unittest.h\"\n  \"*_android_unittest.cc\"\n  \"*\\bandroid/*\"\n  \"*_chromeos.h\"\n  \"*_chromeos.cc\"\n  \"*_chromeos_unittest.h\"\n  \"*_chromeos_unittest.cc\"\n  \"*\\bchromeos/*\"\n]\n\nIf Skia is explicitly managing platform specific files, I think it is safe to disable the filter. I can update the comment.",
